----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCalculator.Ctl3D
Summary
  Determines whether the dialog has a three-dimensional look.
Description
  Use Ctl3D to specify whether controls in the dialog should have a flat or beveled look.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCalculator.Execute
Summary
  Displays the calculator dialog.
Description
  Calling Execute opens the calculator dialog. The calculation result is stored in the Value property.
Return value
  Returns true if user click on the OK button, else false.
See Also
  TJvCalculator.Ctl3D

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCalculator.HelpContext
Summary
  Specifies the context number for online Help.
Description
  The HelpContext property is an integer value that determines which Help screen appears when the
  user requests context-sensitive online Help. If HelpContext is set to the default value of 0, the
  dialog inherits the Help context of its parent.

