@@TJvCalculator.Precision
Summary
  Determines the precision used in formatting the value in the calculator's display.
Description
  Use Precision to set the number of digits beyond the decimal point the value should be formatted to before rounding begins. T
  e default value of Precision is 15 decimal places. Precision <i>does</i> affect the actual
  floating-point value that the calculator uses.
Note
  Precision must be greater than or equal to 2. Trying to set Precision to a value less than 2
  changes the value of Precision to 2.
See Also
  TJvCalculator.CalcDisplay

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCalculator.Title
Summary
  Specifies the text that appears in the calculator dialog box's title bar.
Description
  Use Title to specify the text that appears in the calculator dialog box's title bar.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCalculator.Value
Summary
  Indicates the result of the last calculation.
Description
  The Value property returns the result of the last calculation done in the calculator dialog.
  
  To make a value appear by default in the calculator dialog’s edit box, assign a value to Value in
  the Object
  Inspector or in program code. Programmatic changes to Value have no effect while the dialog is
  active, use CalcDisplay for this purpose.
See Also
  TJvCalculator.CalcDisplay, TJvCalculator.Memory, TJvCalculator.Precision

